@megamissnortheast || Exploring India’s North East Paradise Unexplored with Mega Miss North East Finalist Riya Machahary from Meghalaya 

Supported by - 
Ministry Of Tourism, Government Of India, North East.

“Khulumbai 🙏🏻 

Escape to the Chandisilla, a beautiful picnic spot in Chaibinang, West Garo Hills, Meghalaya, which is an unexplored paradise of Northeast India where nature thrives in its purest form. Surrounded by verdant hills, crystal-clear streams, and enchanting rock formations, this serene picnic spot offers a perfect blend of tranquility and adventure. From natural pools to exploring ancient fossils and refreshing waterfalls, Chandisilla is a haven for those seeking a peaceful getaway amidst breathtaking landscapes ✨

Gwjwntwng 🙏🏻”

@megamisternortheast || Exploring India’s North East Paradise Unexplored with Mega Mister North East Finalist Leonardo Nongpoh from Meghalaya 

Supported by - 
Ministry Of Tourism, Government Of India, North East.

“Khublei! This is Leonardo Nongpoh, proudly representing Meghalaya at Mega Mister North East 2025!

Discover with me the enchanting land of majestic hills, Mawiambei, located in Ribhoi District, just 47 kilometers from Shillong. This breathtaking destination is where clouds fill the sky and serenity reigns, truly living up to its legendary title - “The Abode of the Clouds.”
Join me on this incredible journey as I unveil the raw beauty, rich culture, and warm hospitality of Meghalaya! Let’s celebrate the diversity and splendor of North East India together!”

@megamissnortheast || Exploring India’s North East Paradise Unexplored with Mega Miss North East Finalist Gulpari Khan from Assam

Supported by - 
Ministry Of Tourism, Government Of India, North East.

“Bongaigaon, Birjhora Tea Garden is one of the biggest tea garden. It is also beautiful because of slopping towards Birjhora Hill. This tea Garden produces very good quality first flush Assam Tea.

If you want to take a feel of Assam then you should visit the garden and see the local women plucking tea.
 Introducing you the most visited picnic spot and hill in Bongaigaon “Nakkati hill”, which has an height of (473m/1 552ft a.s.l.) and it is also a hill of himalayas. The people of the localities believe Maa maharani ( Goddess parvati ) had mythological relations with this hill.🪷”

@megamissnortheast || Exploring India’s North East Paradise Unexplored with Mega Miss North East Finalist Kerrener Wahlang Syiemlieh from Meghalaya 

Supported by - 
Ministry Of Tourism, Government Of India, North East.

“In the heart of Meghalaya, Per Umngi offers a serene escape.
Surrounded by lush hills, misty valleys and the gentle hum of the nature, it’s the perfect place for a picnic. The air is fresh, the flowers vibrant and the sound of the nearby stream soothes the soul. Every moment feels like a quite embrace from the earth. 
In Per Umngi, time slows down  allowing you to simple breath and savor the beauty of the world around you.”

Supported by -

“Agartala City,
The chaturdasha (Chibrwi mwtai) tample is a Hindu tample (mandir )
Situated near old Agartala Tripura .
This tample was built in honour of FOURTEEN DEITIES , Together called the chaturdasha Devata , By King Krishna Manikya Debbarma Of TRIPURA.”
